  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nThis happends when sending transactions on xdai chain.\r\n_**Found out that txs with more than 1Gwei are fine**_ \r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Have a xdai node (mine is not a validator) \r\n2. Connect metamask \r\n3. Make tx with **1 Gwei**\r\n4. See error\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nTransaction confirmed\r\n\r\n**LOGS**\r\nDocker log output\r\n`Error when handling ID 2145, eth_sendRawTransaction(someData) | {\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"error\":{\"code\":-32010,\"message\":\"Filtered\"},\"id\":2145}`\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nNode is in docker and configured via:\r\n```\r\nversion: '3.8'\r\nservices:\r\n  nethermind:\r\n    image: nethermind/nethermind\r\n    restart: always\r\n    command: '--config xdai --datadir data --JsonRpc.Enabled true --Metrics.Enabled true'\r\n    volumes:\r\n      - './data:/nethermind/data'\r\n    network_mode: host\r\n```",
